<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  so what makes this ok for non-guild event, but ok for pickup raid ?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
First, let me make clear why it's not ok for a guild event.  Everyone seems to &quot;know&quot; that it is, but WHY is fairly important.  First, it's dishonest.  Hiding your x-loot is something like saying &quot;no, I don't have one.&quot;  We just don't lie to each other.  Second, the goal of distributing treasure on guild events is to do so in a manner that best benefits the guild*.  It'd be rare that the best interets of the guild would be served in the example you set above.<br>
<br>
With regard to a pickup raid, it depends what your committment to the community is, and what the rules of the raid are.  If at that raid, the items are going to be treated like cattle, and split up like sides of beef, then I suggest that the best solution is to act like the mercenary that they &quot;hired&quot; for the event and take mercenaries share of that treasure.  If the organizers of the raid are going to do their best to distribute treasure so that it goes into the hands of people who are going to use it, then do the honest thing and help them by not being dishonest about their items.<br>
<br>
If you are a mercenary, demand a mercenaries share of the reward.<br>
<br>
[*I mentioned the best interests of the guild, and since I touched on it, I wanted to mention that the best interest of the guild was such a vague thing that it's hard to quantify.  Sometimes it means rewarding an outstanding player, or a forgotten person for morale or to demonstrate that we WANT to reward them.  Sometimes it means making sure the warlords can tank better than any 2 of us.  Sometimes it means raising the lowest common denominator by outfitting the worst dressed person.  Sometimes it means rewarding people who do the work.  But it's up to people to make those decisions, because I haven't found a cut-and-dry rule that works for ALL treasure in ALL situations yet.] <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=4868>Palimax Sceleris</a>,
