<br>
The person is not to blame for being a fucknut.  The loot system is.  The most successfull loot system i've ever seen for a pickup dragon raid is, <br>
1) the raid leader announces the loot<br>
2) each person sends the raid leader a tell asking which item they want to random on.  Each person gets ONE chance on ONE item.<br>
3)the raid leader relists all the items with the number of people who are in each lotto<br>
4)everyone is given max 5 minutes to change their mind. (to account for lds and such)<br>
5)items which do not get tells sent about go to the raid leader to distribute as he wishes.<br>
6) all other items get lottoed amoung those who expressed interest, no drop items first, raid leader announces different lotto numbers for each lotto, and who has sent him tells about that item.<br>
<br>
The second most successful method is this:<br>
<br>
All items that drop from the dragon are listed before hand.<br>
Everyone lottoes.<br>
High lotto number gets first pick of the possible drops.  Go on down the lotto list until all possible items are accounted for.<br>
Whatever drops goes to whoever picked it.  If there is a double drop, the second item is lottoed among all who didn't get an item.<br>
<br>
This lotto list can be altered by the raid leader, before hand, by announcing to each person as he's invited to the raid &quot;and if xxx drops, it's going to yyy person, still interested?&quot; before the lotto.<br>
<br>
